  "text": "The increased AI in NF-1 patients is a result of relatively low DTAs. The dark-trough potential is a result of polarisation differences between the apical and basal membranes of RPE cells [CITATION_1] . The significantly lower amplitude of this potential suggests that the mechanisms underlying polarization differences are altered in NF-1.",
